  <h3>Standard Integrals</h3>
  <p>The following standard integrals are all on the formulae list. However, it is useful to know and be able to recognise them to help you recognise when an integral is in a useful form.</p>
  <p class="math">$$
    \begin{eqnarray}
      \int e^{ax} dx &amp;=&amp; \frac{1}{a} e^{ax} + c \\
      \int \frac{dx}{x} = \int \frac{1}{x} dx &amp;=&amp; lnx + c \\
      \int \mathrm{sec}^2 (ax) dx &amp;=&amp; \frac{1}{a} \tan (ax) + c \\
      \int \frac{1}{\sqrt{a^2 - x^2}} dx &amp;=&amp; \sin ^{-1} (\frac{x}{a}) + c \\
      \int \frac{1}{a^2 + x^2} dx &amp;=&amp; \frac{1}{a} \tan ^{-1} (\frac{x}{a}) + c \\
    \end{eqnarray}
  $$</p>
